% References.bib — centralized bibliography for method RATIONALE documents.
%
% Every `<method>.RATIONALE.md` that cites a paper or external claim references
% an entry here by its BibTeX key (written `[@key]` in the RATIONALE's
% References section). `scripts/check_rationale_structure.py` audits the
% cross-links: a `[@key]` with no matching entry, or an entry with no working
% URL / DOI / arXiv id, fails CI.
%
% Kept in BibTeX (not inline prose) so the seasonal research review and the
% auto-paper generator can reuse the same entries without re-curating them.
%
% Internal firm artifacts (the Embedding Geometry Conjecture experiments, the
% Quintin Hypothesis benchmark, the Householder ablation report) are *not*
% papers and are referenced in RATIONALE prose by repo-relative path rather
% than by a key here.

